sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant UI as Client/UI
    participant API as ComplianceController
    participant ISO as iso27001_controls.json
    participant CHK as checks.json
    participant OAUTH as OAuthService
    participant STR as ToolExecutionStrategy
    participant MCP as McpClient
    participant RES as ToolResolver
    participant REST as RestToolFallbackClient
    participant EVAL as EvaluationEngine

    UI->>API: POST /api/compliance/evaluate { controlId: "8.28", provider: "github", repoName }
    API->>ISO: Load control 8.28
    ISO-->>API: checks = ["secure_review_check"]
    API->>CHK: Load check definition
    CHK-->>API: tool.mcp.github + tool.rest.github + evaluation_logic(min_reviews)

    API->>OAUTH: getAccessToken("github", tenantId)
    OAUTH-->>API: access token

    loop For each candidate tool needed by secure_review_check
        API->>STR: executeTool(provider, toolName, params, preference)
        STR->>MCP: listTools(provider)  // live MCP exposure
        MCP-->>STR: mcpExposedTools[]
        STR->>RES: resolve(provider, toolName, mcpExposedTools, preference)
        RES->>CHK: Read check tool map (mcp/rest for github)
        CHK-->>RES: mapped mcp/rest tool names

        alt MCP tool is mapped and exposed
            STR->>MCP: callTool(mapped mcp tool, params)
            MCP-->>STR: evidence payload
        else REST fallback is mapped
            STR->>REST: callTool(mapped rest tool, params)
            REST-->>STR: evidence payload
        else No executable strategy
            STR-->>API: error (mode = none)
        end
    end

    API->>EVAL: evaluate(controlId=8.28, evidence, logic=min_reviews)
    EVAL-->>API: status + findings + metadata
    API-->>UI: control result (PASS/FAIL/UNDETERMINED, api_call, reasons)
